{
  "page": "King of Yronwood",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>King of Yronwood</b> was a title used by monarchs from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Yronwood\" title=\"House Yronwood\">House Yronwood</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Yronwood\" title=\"Yronwood\">Yronwood</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Known_Kings_of_Yronwood\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Kings of Yronwood</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King_of_Yronwood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ruling from <a href=\"/index.php/Yronwood\" title=\"Yronwood\">Yronwood</a> in the southeastern <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Mountains\" title=\"Red Mountains\">Red Mountains</a>, the Kings of Yronwood once controlled half of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \nTheir last king was <a href=\"/index.php/Yorick_V_Yronwood\" title=\"Yorick V Yronwood\">Yorick V Yronwood</a>, whose vassals included, among others, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackmont\" title=\"House Blackmont\">Blackmonts</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Blackmont\" title=\"Blackmont\">Blackmont</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Jordayne\" title=\"House Jordayne\">Jordaynes</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Tor\" title=\"Tor\">Tor</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Qorgyle\" title=\"House Qorgyle\">Qorgyles</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Sandstone\" title=\"Sandstone\">Sandstone</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Wyl\" title=\"House Wyl\">Wyls</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Wyl_(castle)\" title=\"Wyl (castle)\">Wyl</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_then_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_then_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The Yronwoods were defeated by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\">House Martell</a> during <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria%27s_War\" title=\"Nymeria&#39;s War\">Nymeria's War</a>, however, with Yorick forced to join the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_coming_of_the_rhoynar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_coming_of_the_rhoynar.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Kings_of_Yronwood\">Known Kings of Yronwood</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King_of_Yronwood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Kings of Yronwood\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Olyvar_Yronwood\" title=\"Olyvar Yronwood\">Olyvar Yronwood</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Yorick_V_Yronwood\" title=\"Yorick V Yronwood\">Yorick V Yronwood</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King_of_Yronwood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Before <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria\" title=\"Nymeria\">Nymeria</a> came, the Kings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yronwood\" title=\"Yronwood\">Yronwood</a> were the most powerful house in all of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>—far greater than the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\">Martells</a> of the time. They ruled half of Dorne—a fact that, to this day, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Yronwood\" title=\"House Yronwood\">Yronwoods</a> let no one forget.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King_of_Yronwood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Bloodroyal\" title=\"Bloodroyal\">Bloodroyal</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Stone_Way\" title=\"Lord of the Stone Way\">Lord of the Stone Way</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_the_Green_Hills\" title=\"Master of the Green Hills\">Master of the Green Hills</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_Stone_Way\" title=\"Warden of the Stone Way\">Warden of the Stone Way</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King_of_Yronwood&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_queer_customs_of_the_south.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; 